s%20ambitious%20climate%20goals%20for%202030%2C%20and%20Germany%20and%20Italy%20are%20largely%20to%20blame.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20two%20countries%20are%20so%20far%20off%20track%20of%20cutting%20greenhouse%20gas%20emissions%20in%20industries%20like%20transportation%20and%20buildings%20that%20they%20could%20be%20forced%20to%20spend%20upwards%20of%20%2416.1%20billion%20(%E2%82%AC15%20billion)%20on%20carbon%20credits%20to%20comply%20with%20an%20EU%20law%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.transportenvironment.org%2Farticles%2F12-eu-countries-fail-to-comply-with-2030-national-climate-targets-new-study%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20research%20by%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ET%26amp%3BE%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20nonprofit%20that%20advocates%20for%20cleaner%20transportation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20just%20one%20problem%3A%20Germany%20and%20Italy%20could%20eat%20up%20the%20majority%20of%20credits%20available%20across%20the%20EU%2C%20setting%20up%20a%20costly%20bidding%20war%20by%20other%20countries%20that%20also%20miss%20their%20climate%20goals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGermany%20and%20Italy%20are%20eating%20up%20all%20available%20carbon%20credits%20from%20their%20neighbours%2C%20leaving%20them%20stranded%20and%20at%20risk%20of%20legal%20proceedings%2C%26quot%3B%20Sofie%20Defour%2C%20climate%20director%20at%20T%26amp%3BE%2C%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%20%26quot%3BThe%20German%20government%20will%20soon%20have%20to%20face%20its%20citizens%20asking%20for%20even%20more%20money%20and%20deepening%20the%20budget%20crisis%20yet%20further%2C%20to%20make%20up%20for%20their%20weak%20policies.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20EU%20climate%20law%2C%20known%20as%20the%20Effort%20Sharing%20Regulation%2C%20sets%20binding%20emissions%20reduction%20targets%20for%20each%20of%20the%20bloc's%2027%20countries.%20The%20overall%20goal%20is%20to%20slash%20emissions%20by%2040%25%20by%202030%2C%20compared%20to%202005%20levels.%20The%20law%20applies%20to%20industries%20like%