iving.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efar%20deadlier%20roads%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20other%20rich%20countries.%20The%20US%20has%20seen%20road%20deaths%20spike%20recently%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0in%202021%2C%20traffic%20fatalities%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2022%2F05%2F17%2Fus-traffic-deaths-hit-16-year-high-in-2021-dot-says.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DU.S.%2520traffic%2520deaths%2520reached%2520a%2C2021%252C%2520according%2520to%2520government%2520estimates%26amp%3Btext%3DNHTSA%252C%2520a%2520federal%2520vehicle%2520safety%2Chave%2520died%2520during%2520a%2520crash.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehit%20a%2016-year%20high%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20in%202023%2C%20deaths%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbes.com%2Fsites%2Ftanyamohn%2F2024%2F02%2F27%2Ftraffic-crash-deaths-in-2023-remain-at-devastatingly-high-level%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E13.6%25%20higher%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20in%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAustria's%20director%20general%20of%20transportation%2C%20Vera%20Hofbauer%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2024-06-19%2Faustria-aims-to-curb-crashes-with-crackdown-on-super-speeders%3Fsrnd%3Dall%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20Bloomberg%20News%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20new%20law%20hasn't%20been%20on%20the%20books%20for%20long%20enough%20to%20measure%20its%20impact%2C%20but%20it's%20already%20being%20felt.%20Just%20hours%20after%20the%20law%20went%20into%20effect%2C%20the%20government%20confiscated%20the%20car%20of%20a%20super%20speeder%2C%20she%20said.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAustria%20experienced%204.1%20road%20deaths%20for%20every%20100%2C000%20people%20in%202022.%20Hofbauer%20argued%20that%20%26quot%3Bdrastic%20measures%26quot%3B%20must%20be%20taken%20to%20stop%20drivers%20who%20%26quot%3Bare%20using%20their%20car%20like%20a%20weapon.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAustrian%20officials%20aren't%20alone%20in%20cracking%20down%20on%20dangerous%20driving.%20A%20slew%20of%20European%20countries%20have%20implemented%20the%20world's%20strictest%20road%20safety%20regulations.%20In%20several%20countries%2C%20speeding%20tickets%20are%20calculated%20based%20on%20the%20driver's%20income%2C%20so%20the%20wealthier%20the%20driver%20is%2C%20the%20steeper%20the%20fine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Switzerland%2C%20speeding%20tickets%20have%20been%20calculated%20based%20on%20both%20income%20and%20wealth%20since%202007%2C%20when%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nbcnews.com%2Fid%2Fwbna34792272%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evoters%20decided%20to%20crack%20down%20on%20wealthy%20speeders%3C%2Fa%3E.%20One%20driver%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-10960230%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efined%20more%20than%20%241%20million%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202010%20for%20driving%20his%20Mercedes%20sports%20car%20about%20180%20mph%20in%20a%2075%20mph%20zone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%20in%20Finland%2C%20a%20multimillionaire%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2023%2Fjun%2F06%2Ffinnish-businessman-hit-with-121000-speeding-fine%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eslapped%20with%20a%20%E2%82%AC121%2C000%20ticket%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0about%20%24130%2C000%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0for%20going%20about%2018%20miles%20per%20hour%20above%20the%20speed%20limit%20in%20a%2050%20kph%20(31%20mph)%20zone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20European%20Union%20is%20also%20cracking%20down.%20In%202022%2C%20the%20European%20Commission%20mandated%20that%20beginning%20in%202024%2C%20all%20new%20cars%20have%20technology%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.autoweek.com%2Fnews%2Findustry-news%2Fa40543584%2Fanti-speeding-tech-mandatory-in-european-union%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ealerts%20drivers%20when%20they%20exceed%20the%20speed%20limit%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20measure%20is%20predicted%20to%20cut%20road%20deaths%20by%2020%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20laws%20seem%20to%20be%20working%3A%20countries%20that%20have%20imposed%20the%20strictest%20road%20rules%20also%20have%20the%20safest%20roads.%20Switzerland%20has%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.itf-oecd.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fswitzerland-road-safety.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2.6%20road%20deaths%20per%20100%2C000%20people%3C%2Fa%3E%20each%20year%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0among%20the%20lowest%20in%20the%20world%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20its%20fatalities%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Froad-safety.transport.ec.europa.eu%2Fsystem%2Ffiles%2F2023-02%2Ferso-country-overview-2023-switzerland_1.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efallen%20faster%20than%20the%20EU%20average%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20the%20last%20decade.%20By%20comparison%2C%20the%20US%20road%20death%20rate%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iihs.org%2Ftopics%2Ffatality-statistics%2Fdetail%2Fstate-by-state%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E12.8%20per%20100%2C000%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSometimes%20you%20have%20to%20try%20measures%20which%20sound%20strange%20at%20first%2C%20and%20which%20create%20new%20legal%20questions%20that%20you%20must%20answer%2C%26quot%3B%20Hofbauer%20told%20Bloomberg.%20%26quot%3BBut%20I%20think%20we%20should%20try%20everything%20we%20can%20to%20reduce%20crashes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspeeding-driving-austria-government-confiscate-sell-car-europe-2024-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1718841645000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66735ca4087acd2be9b4ee38%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspeeding-driving-austria-government-confiscate-sell-car-europe-2024-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20other%20European%20countries%2C%20including%20Switzerland%20and%20Finland%2C%20speeders%20are%20fined%20a%20percentage%20of%20their%20income.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40in