ed%20my%20husband%20when%20we%20were%20both%2021%20years%20old.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20a%20busboy%2C%20and%20I%20was%20a%20waitress.%20We%20lived%20in%20a%20tiny%20apartment%2C%20went%20nowhere%20but%20the%20restaurant%20where%20we%20both%20worked%2C%20and%20lived%20off%20of%20frozen%20tilapia%20and%20rice.%20Thanks%20to%20parental%20assistance%2C%20my%20husband%20was%20still%20in%20college%2C%20but%20I%20couldn't%20afford%20to%20finish%20my%20degree%20because%20we%20didn't%20have%20the%20money%20and%20someone%20needed%20to%20pull%20double%20shifts.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20we%20were%20broke.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20with%20a%20few%20smart%20financial%20moves%2C%20a%20generous%20grandmother%20helping%20us%20with%20our%20first%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fhow-much-down-payment-for-a-house%5C%22%3Emortgage%20down%20payment%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20several%20odd%20jobs%2C%20and%20a%20lot%20of%20perseverance%2C%20our%20financial%20position%20has%20improved%20over%20the%20last%2011%20years.%20My%20husband%20finished%20his%20degree%2C%20and%20then%20I%20finished%20mine.%20He's%20climbed%20the%20corporate%20ladder.%20We%20sold%20our%20first%20house%20for%20twice%20what%20we%20paid%20for%20it%2C%20and%20I%20found%20a%20way%20to%20make%20my%20English%20degree%20pay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20process%20has%20been%20long%20and%20grinding%2C%20and%20it's%20included%20a%20lot%20of%20lost%20hair%20and%20scary%20living%20situations%2C%20but%20one%20day%2C%20as%20I%20wrote%20my%20grocery%20shopping%20list%2C%20I%20realized%20that%20at%20some%20point%2C%20we%20had%20traded%20our%20frozen%20tilapia%20for%20fresh%2C%20wild-caught%20salmon.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20we've%20made%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20financial%20lesson%20we%20learned%20years%20ago%20that%20helps%20us%20save%20money%20today%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOK%2C%20%26quot%3Bmade%20it%26quot%3B%20might%20be%20an%20overstatement%3B%20we're%20eating%20fresh%20fish%2C%20not%20climbing%20aboard