hanged%20since%201999%2C%20according%20to%20a%20new%20study.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMeals%20remain%20high%20in%20processed%20foods%20that%20can%20increase%20a%20person's%20risk%20of%20disease.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDitching%20sugary%20drinks%20and%20eating%20two%20fewer%20processed%20meals%20a%20week%20could%20help.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAmericans%20are%20eating%20healthier%20than%20in%20previous%20years%2C%20but%20they%20still%20have%20a%20long%20way%20to%20go%2C%20according%20to%20a%20researcher%20who%20studies%20food%20as%20medicine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDr.%20Dariush%20Mozaffarian%2C%20director%20of%20the%20Food%20is%20Medicine%20Institute%20at%20Tufts%20University%20in%20Boston%2C%20co-authored%20a%20study%20on%20the%20quality%20of%20nearly%2052%2C000%20American%20adults'%20diets%20between%201999%20and%202020.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.acpjournals.org%2Fdoi%2F10.7326%2FM24-0190%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresults%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20published%20online%20Tuesday%20in%20the%20Annals%20of%20Internal%20Medicine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMozaffarian%20and%20his%20co-author%2C%20Junxiu%20Liu%2C%20examined%20data%20from%20the%20National%20Health%20and%20Nutrition%20Examination%20Survey%20and%20found%20that%20the%20American%20diet%20has%20remained%20nearly%20the%20same%20over%20the%20past%20two%20decades.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBetween%201999%20and%202020%2C%2010.5%25%20of%20study%20participants%20transitioned%20from%20%26quot%3Bpoor%26quot%3B%20diets%20to%20healthier%20diets%20with%20more%20fruits%2C%20vegetables%2C%20and%20whole%20grains%20and%20less%20sodium%2C%20processed%20meat%2C%20and%20saturated%20fat.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20only%201%25%20of%20study%20participants%20ate%20an%20%26quot%3Bideal%26quot%3B%20diet%20%E2%80%94%204%20to%205%20cups%20of%20fruits%20and%20vegetables%20daily%2C%20plus%20beans%2C%20whole%20grains%2C%20and%20nuts%20%E2%80%94%20during%20that%20same%20time%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20often%20ask%20me%2C%20'Well%2C%20if%20the%20diet's%20slowly%20improving%2C%20why%20is%20obesity%20and%20diabetes%20still%20going%20up%3F'%20It's%20still%20going%20up%20because%20only%201.58%25%20of%20Americans%20have%20an%20ideal%20diet.%20We%20still%20have%20a%20long%20way%20to%20go%2C%26quot%3B%20Mozaffarian%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2F2024%2F06%2F17%2Fhealth%2Fimprove-diet-quality-tips-wellness%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECNN%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20stalled%20as%20a%20nation%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20does%20not%20bode%20well%20for%20our%20health.%20If%20I%20was%20grading%20America%20on%20its%20diet%2C%20I'd%20give%20it%20a%20D%E2%80%94just%20up%20from%20an%20F%2C%26quot%3B%20Mozaffarian%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22645b3920-d5b9-4d14-868f-c48fe2d6ed79%5C%22%3EWhy%20are%20Americans%20failing%20in%20the%20diet%20department%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETypically%2C%20the%20American%20diet%20consists%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-processed-food-2019-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eultra-processed%20foods%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20foods%20high%20in%20salt%20and%20sugar.%20These%20foods%20can%20increase%20a%20person's%20risk%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcancer-prevention-lifestyle-changes-dietitian-advice-healthy-eating-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecancer%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fscientists-making-ultra-processed-foods-healthier-in-major-new-study-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eheart%20disease%2C%20stroke%2C%20and%20early%20death%3C%2Fa%3EAccordingng%20to%20Heidi%20Silver%2C%20a%20registered%20dietitian%20and%20director%20of%20the%20Vanderbilt%20Diet%2C%20Body%20Composition%2C%20and%20Human%20Metabolism%20Core%20at%20Vanderbilt%20University%20Medical%20Center%20in%20Nashvil%2C%20factors%20like%20food%20insecurity%20and%20poverty%20have%20contributed%20to%20