ny%20of%20today's%20consumer%20healthcare%20conversations%2C%20there's%20a%20mounting%20concern%20for%20a%20particularly%20vulnerable%20group%3A%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPharmaceutical%20giants%20Eli%20Lilly%20and%20Novo%20Nordisk%20have%20been%20running%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fweight-loss-drugs-for-kids-6-years-old-mounjaro-trial-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eclinical%20trials%20on%20children%20with%20obesity%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20are%20as%20young%20as%206%20to%20understand%20how%20this%20class%20of%20drugs%2C%20called%20GLP-1s%2C%20could%20affect%20their%20health%2C%20Business%20Insider's%20Hilary%20Brueck%20previously%20reported.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20January%202023%2C%20the%20American%20Academy%20of%20Pediatrics%20(AAP)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpublications.aap.org%2Fpediatrics%2Farticle%2F151%2F2%2Fe2022060640%2F190443%2FClinical-Practice-Guideline-for-the-Evaluation-and%3Fautologincheck%3Dredirected%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecommended%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20healthcare%20providers%20offer%20weight-loss%20medications%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20lifestyle%20adjustments%2C%20to%20treat%20obesity%20in%20children%2012%20and%20older.%20However%2C%20not%20all%20health%20professionals%20agree%20with%20the%20AAP's%20recommendation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Preventive%20Services%20Task%20Force%20%E2%80%94%20a%20panel%20of%20more%20than%20a%20dozen%20doctors%20and%20public%20health%20experts%20from%20various%20academic%20institutions%20%E2%80%94%20issued%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjamanetwork.com%2Fjournals%2Fjama%2Ffullarticle%2F2820244%3FguestAccessKey%3D92173756-56de-4d43-bcc4-56cf8701328f%26utm_source%3DFor_The_Media%26utm_medium%3Dreferral%26utm_campaign%3Dftm_links%26utm_content%3Dtfl%26utm_term%3D061824%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estatement%3C%2Fa%3E%20pushing%20for%20drug-free%20weight-loss%20interventions%20for%20children%20who%20are%206%20and%20older%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20believe%20we%20need%20more%20evidence%20to%20be%20able%20to%20make%20a%20recommendation%20for%20or%20against%20medications%20in%20children%20and%20adolescents%2C%26quot%3B%20Wanda%20Nicholson%2C%20the%20task%20force's%20chair%20and%20senior%20associate%20dean%20of%20diversity%20and%20inclusion%20at%20the%20George%20Washington%20University%20School%20of%20Public%20Health%2C%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.statnews.com%2F2024%2F06%2F18%2Fchildren-obesity-behavioral-therapy-wegovy-recommendations%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESTAT%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20there%20were%20trials%20evaluating%20the%20effectiveness%20of%20FDA-approved%20medications%2C%20there%20was%20a%20limited%20number%20of%20trials%20per%20medication%20from%20our%20review.%20And%20in%20addition%2C%20there%20was%20limited%20evidence%20on%20weight%20loss%20maintenance%20after%20medications%20were%20discontinued%20in%20children%2C%26quot%3B%20Nicholson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bf3f2edf-a3b8-4d06-b0e1-aecb49fa32b3%5C%22%3ELifestyle%20interventions%20are%20still%20preferred%20by%20doctors%20over%20drugs%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGLP-1%20drugs%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsemaglutide-ozempic-disgusted-favorite-foods-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWeGovy%20and%20Ozempic%3C%2Fa%3E%20contain%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsemaglutide-how-does-drug-work-for-weight-loss-diabetes-2021-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esemaglutide%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20substance%20that%20increases%20a%20person's%20insulin%2C%20the%20natural%20hormone%20that%20regulates%20blood%20sugar%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-ozempic-wegovy-actually-work-telling-brain-to-feel-full-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etells%20the%20body%20when%20it's%20full%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20injectable%20drugs%20have%20proven%20successful%20as%20weight-loss%20interventions%20for%20adults%20with%20obesity%2C%20early%20research%20shows.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20this%20class%20of%20drugs%20has%20its%20limitations.%20Many%20GLP-1%20users%20have%20reported%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fozempic-wegovy-users-grapple-with-quitting-weight-loss-drugs-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eweight%20gain%20after%20ceasing%20GLP-1%20use%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20while%20others%20have%20mentioned%20side%20effects%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fozempic-wegovy-semaglutide-weight-loss-drug-side-effects-pooping-pants-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ediarrhea%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmounjaro-lawsuit-alleges-stomach-is-paralyzed-from-glp-1-use-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bparalyzed%26quot%3B%20stomachs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmounjaro-vs-ozempic-side-effects-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehair%20loss%2C%20and%20nausea%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Preventive%20Services%20Task%20Force%20voiced%20concern%20for%20these%20potential%20side%20effects%20in%20children%2C%20as%20well%20as%20an%20excessive%20focus%20on%20weight%20instead%20of%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENicholson%20said%20clinicians%20have%20used%20lifestyle%20interventions%2C%20like%20nutrition%20and%20exercise%20plans%2C%20to%20help%20children%20with%20obesity%20lose%20weight%20and%20reduce%20risk%20factors%20like%20hypertension%2C%20diabetes%2C%20and%20liver%20disease.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20AAP's%20and%20the%20US%20Preventive%20Services%20Task%20Force's%20recommendations%20overlap%2C%20according%20to%20Amanda%20Staiano%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20of%20pediatric%20obesity%20and%20health%20behavior%20at%20the%20Pennington%20Biomedical%20Research%20Center%20of%20Louisiana%20State%20University.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20AAP%20explicitly%20states%20that%20drugs%20should%20not%20be%20a%20monotherapy.%20They%20are%20an%20adjunct%20to%20be%20used%20in%20combination%20with%20intensive%20health%20behavior%20and%20lifestyle%20treatment%2C%26quot%3B%20Staino%2C%20who%20was%20on%20the%20AAP's%20clinical%20practice%20guideline%20authorship%20committee%2C%20told%20STAT.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-doctors-warn-against-glp1s-wegovy-ozempic-children-2024-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1718821426000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66731155087acd2be9b4ea24%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-doctors-warn-against-glp1s-wegovy-ozempic-children-2024-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20US%20Preventive%20Services%20Task%20Force%20warned%20against%20giving%20children%206%20and%20older%20buzzy%20weight-loss%20drugs.%20The%20AAP%20previously%20recommended%20it.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jnaftulin%40businessinsider.com%20(Julia%20Naftulin)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-doctors-warn-against-glp1s-wegovy-ozempic-children-2024-6%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Fertility%20expert%20Leslie%20Schrock%20explains%20why%20embryonic%20personhood%20will%20never%20work%20in%20practice%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226720%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Leslie%20Schrock%2C%20a%20fertility%20investor%20and%20author.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66730f14a76074d191cd3bce%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224480%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELeslie%20Schrock%2C%20an%20investor%2C%20author%2C%20and%20fertility%20expert.%3Cp%3ELeslie%20Schrock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EIVF%20is%20under%20increasing%20scrutiny%20by%20conservative%20groups%20after%20the%20fall%20of%20Roe%20v.%20Wade.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThey%20take%20particular%20issue%20with%20the%20treatment's%20destruction%20of%20embryos.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOne%20author%20and%20fertility%20expert%20explains%20why%20these%20views%20won't%20work%20in%20practice.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202020%2C%20a%20hospital%20patient%20in%20Alabama%20wandered%20into%20a%20storage%20room%2C%20removed%20embryos%20from%20tanks%20of%20liquid%20nitrogen%2C%20and%20dropped%20them%20on%20the%20floor.%20Couples%20sued%20over%20wrongful%20death.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20February%2C%20the%20Alabama%20Supreme%20Court%20sided%20with%20the%20couples%2C%20ruling%20that%20the%20frozen%20embryos%20could%20legally%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2024%2F02%2F20%2Fhealth%2Fivf-alabama-abortion.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econsidered%3C%2Fa%3E%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20before%20birth%2C%20all%20human%20beings%20have%20the%20image%20of%20God%2C%20and%20their%20lives%20cannot%20be%20destroyed%20without%20effacing%20his%20glory%2C%26quot%3B%20Chief%20Justice%20Tom%20Parker%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2024%2F02%2F20%2Fhealth%2Fivf-alabama-abortion.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrote%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20concurring%20opinion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ruling%20not%20only%20created%20chaos%20for%20the%20state's%20fertility%20doctors%20%E2%80%94%20it%20kicked%20off%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fsenate-ivf-alabama-reproductive-care-460d099153d3faf548e9326ff17dbae6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enational%3C%2Fa%3E%20debate%20over%20access%20to%20IVF.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20treatment%20helps%20women%20get%20pregnant%20by%20combining%20eggs%20and%20sperm%20in%20a%20lab%20setting.%20The%20goal%20is%20to%20create%20multiple%20embryos%2C%20with%20the%20hope%20of%20creating%20just%20one%20successful%20pregnancy.%20The%20rest%20might%20be%20thrown%20away%20or%20stored%20for%20future%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20a%20world%20without%20the%20protections%20afforded%20by%20Roe%20v.%20Wade%2C%20many%20fear%20%26quot%3Bfetal%20personhood%26quot%3B%20laws%2C%20which%20give%20fetuses%20and%20potentially%20embryos%20the%20legal%20rights%20of%20a%20person%2C%20could%20complicate%20the%20IVF%20process%20for%20patients%20by%20raising%20the%20question%3A%20does%20throwing%20away%20excess%20embryos%20constitute%20murder%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESolutions%20like%20making%20one%20embryo%20at%20a%20time%2C%20for%20example%2C%20won't%20work%2C%20Leslie%20Schrock%2C%20an%20investor%2C%20author%2C%20and%20fertility%20expert%2C%20told%20BI%20in%20an%20interview.%20IVF%20requires%20making%20several%20embryos%20at%20once%2C%20as%20it%20mimics%20the%20very%20inefficiency%20that%20takes%20place%20naturally%20in%20our%20own%20bodies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222a33c00a-6165-496b-b6be-6771c643ccbb%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ENatural%20human%20biology%20isn't%20perfect%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20week%2C%20Senate%20Republicans%20voted%20against%20a%20bill%20that%20would%20protect%20IVF%20access.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20Southern%20Baptists%2C%20at%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2024%2F06%2F12%2Fus%2Fivf-vote-southern-baptists.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enational%20conference%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20voted%20to%20oppose%20the%20use%20of%20IVF%2C%20but%20the%20resolution%20didn't%20explicitly%20oppose%20the%20creation%20of%20embryos%20that%20way%20%E2%80%94%20just%20their%20destruction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20these%20organizations%20have%20signaled%20that%20they%20believe%20life%20begins%20when%20%26quot%3Bsperm%20meets%20egg%2C%26quot%3B%20Schrock%20said.%20If%20you%20look%20at%20IVF%20through%20that%20lens%20alone%2C%20you%20would%20naturally%20believe%20that%20discarding%20embryos%20isn't%20okay.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20no%20way%20around%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20our%20natural%20biology%20discards%20embryos%20all%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20embryos%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC5443340%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econceived%20naturally%3C%2Fa%3E%20don't%20survive%20in%20the%20human%20body.%20Among%20those%20that%20become%20successful%20pregnancies%2C%20one%20in%20four%20end%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fhealth%2F2022%2F08%2F02%2Fmiscarriage-risk-pregnancy%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emiscarriage%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20biology%20of%20creating%20humans%20is%20fundamentally%20flawed%2C%26quot%3B%20Schrock%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20perfect.%20It's%20not%20like%20every%20time%20a%20sperm%20and%20egg%20meets%2C%20you%20get%20a%20viable%20pregnancy%2C%20much%20less%20a%20live%20birth.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIVF%20mimics%20this%20natural%20funnel.%20Not%20every%20fertilized%20egg%20will%20turn%20into%20an%20embryo%3B%20not%20every%20embryo%20will%20show%20up%20normal%20in%20genetic%20testing%3B%20and%20even%20the%20embryos%20that%20make%20it%20that%20far%20don't%20always%20transfer%20into%20the%20uterus%20successfully%2C%20Schrock%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaking%20one%20embryo%20at%20a%20time%20would%20decrease%20success%20rates%2C%20extend%20wait%20times%2C%20and%20put%20further%20demands%20on%20IVF's%20lab%20workers%2C%20which%20are%20already%20in%20short%20supply%2C%20per%20Schrock%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fconceivable-automating-ivf-fertility-robots-ai-startup-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBI's%20reporting%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20lot%20of%20loss%20along%20the%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20purposeful%20loss%2C%20it's%20not%20wasteful%2C%20it's%20not%20on%20purpose.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a51d0d76-ebb3-461f-8c55-d317ccea3d5e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EPeople%20aren't%20really%20choosing%20IVF%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20US%2C%20the%20treatment%2C%20which%20usually%20isn't%20covered%20by%20insurance%2C%20costs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdbsable.medium.com%2Fhaving-an-ivf-baby-vs-buying-a-toyota-847a834c3b52%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20a%20Toyota%20Corolla.%20Meaning%20most%20IVF%20patients%20are%20either%20wealthy%20or%20taking%20out%20loans.%20(Yes%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fconceivable-automating-ivf-fertility-robots-ai-startup-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewe%20live%20in%20a%20society%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20which%20your%20ability%20to%20have%20a%20baby%20can%20depend%20on%20your%20credit%20score.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWomen%20usually%20have%20to%20undergo%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fconceivable-automating-ivf-fertility-robots-ai-startup-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etwo%20or%20three%20cycles%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20become%20pregnant%2C%20extending%20the%20financial%20and%20emotional%20costs%20of%20being%20a%20fertility%20patient.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConservative%20groups%20can%20misunderstand%20that%20people%20who%20take%20this%20treatment%20on%2C%20per%20Schrock%2C%20are%20doing%20so%20because%20it's%20medically%20necessary%20to%20start%20a%20family%20%E2%80%94%20not%20because%20they%20want%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchrock%20herself%20nearly%20pursued%20IVF%20after%20suffering%20a%20miscarriage%20and%20medically%20necessary%20abortion.%20In%20the%20latter%20case%2C%20the%20fetus%20had%20stopped%20growing%20at%20around%20twelve%20weeks.%20At%20that%20point%2C%20she%20hadn't%20had%20children%20yet%2C%20and%20the%20choice%20%E2%80%94%20or%20lack%20thereof%2C%20rather%20%E2%80%94%20blew%20her%20mind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20not%20something%20I%20wanted%2C%20it%20was%20not%20something%20I%20had%20ever%20even%20imagined%20was%20possible%2C%20and%20it%20was%20the%20hardest%20experience%20of%20my%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20still%20visceral%20to%20this%20day%2C%20but%20medically%20speaking%2C%20I%20didn't%20have%20another%20option.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDeeply%20personal%20challenges%20are%20often%20where%20the%20IVF%20journey%20begins%20%E2%80%94%20and%2C%20sadly%2C%20ends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20year%2C%20one%20patient%2C%20who%20asked%20not%20to%20be%20named%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fconceivable-automating-ivf-fertility-robots-ai-startup-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edescribed%3C%2Fa%3E%20her%20experience%20with%20fertility%20care%20to%20BI%20as%20a%20never-ending%20series%20of%20arbitrary%20choices%2C%20marked%20by%20a%20miscarriage%20and%20the%20end%20of%20her%20relationship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20don't%20just%20go%20into%20the%20process%20because%20it's%20fun%2C%26quot%3B%20Schrock%20told%20BI%2C%20adding%3A%20%26quot%3BIt's%20hard%2C%20it's%20disruptive%2C%20it's%20emotional.%20It%20is%20painful%20in%20many%20cases.%20And%20it%20does%20not%20always%20end%20with%20a%20healthy%20pregnancy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchrock%2C%20who%20has%20written%20about%20her%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fleslieschrock.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexperiences%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20books%2C%20felt%20shame%20for%20years%2C%20wondering%20where%20she%20went%20wrong.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20you%20know%20what%2C%20it's%20just%20biology%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20taken%20me%20years%20to%20get%20to%20that.%20But%20it%20wasn't%20my%20fault%2C%20though.%20It%20wasn't%20my%20fault%20that%20it%20happened.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fconservatives-southern-baptist-embryonic-personhood-ivf-access-2024-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22publish